    description:"Modular Arithmeitc\n\nPerform arithmetic operations under modulo (typically mod 10^9 + 7).\n\nKey properties:\n- (a + b) % m = ((a%m) + (b%m)) % m\n- (a * b) % m = ((a%m) * (b%m)) % m\n- Modular inverse: a^(-1) mod m = a^(m-2) mod m (when m is prime)\n\nUse modular exponentiation for large powers.\n\nDifficulty: Medium | Topic: Mathematics > Modular Arithmetic",
