    description:"Design LRU Cache\n\nDesign a cache system like LRU (Least Recently Used) or LFU (Least Frequently Used).\n\nLRU Cache: Use a hash map + doubly linked list. Get and Put in O(1).\n- Get: Move accessed node to front (most recent)\n- Put: Add to front. If full, remove tail (least recent)\n\nLFU Cache: Track frequency counts + recency within same frequency.\n\nDifficulty: Medium | Topic: Linked List > Design Cache",
    examples:[{input:"LRU capacity=2: put(1,1), put(2,2), get(1), put(3,3)",output:"After put(3,3): evicts key 2 (least recently used). Cache: {1:1, 3:3}"}],
