    description:"Steps Reduce to 0\n\nCount the number of set bits (1s) in the binary representation of an integer (also called Hamming Weight or popcount).\n\nApproach 1: Check each bit using n & 1, then right shift.\nApproach 2: Brian Kernighan's trick — n = n & (n-1) removes the lowest set bit. Count iterations.\n\nTime: O(number of set bits).\n\nDifficulty: Easy | Topic: Bit Manipulation > Hamming Weight",
    examples:[{input:"n = 11 (binary: 1011)",output:"3 (three 1-bits)"},{input:"n = 128 (binary: 10000000)",output:"1"}],
