    description:"Topological Sort\n\nOrder vertices of a Directed Acyclic Graph (DAG) such that for every edge u→v, u comes before v.\n\nKahn's Algorithm (BFS): Process nodes with in-degree 0, reduce neighbors' in-degrees.\nDFS approach: Post-order DFS, then reverse.\n\nApplications: task scheduling, course prerequisites, build systems.\n\nDifficulty: Medium | Topic: Graphs > Topological Sort",
